<div id="outline-container-org0cb9d2d" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org0cb9d2d"><i>q</i>-Frobenius distributions</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org0cb9d2d">
<p>
Here is some graphical data of distrubutions of the sequences of normalized traces of the powers of Frobenius for abelian surfaces defined over \(\mathbf{F}_2\).
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org34b9112" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org34b9112">Abelian surfaces over the field with two elements</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org34b9112">
<p>
There are 35 isogeny classes of abelian surfaces over \(\mathbf{F}_2\). For each isogeny class \(A\), we consider the Frobenius polynomial \(P_A(T)\) with complex roots \(\alpha_1, \alpha_2, \alpha_3, \alpha_4\). Here we plot the frequency histograms for the sequence 
</p>
\begin{equation*}
    x_r = \frac{\alpha_1^r + \alpha_2^r + \alpha_3^r + \alpha_4^r}{2^{r/2}} \in [-4,4], \text{ for } r \geq 1.
\end{equation*} 
</div>

